## Authentication

All requests must include a Bearer token in the Authorization header.


Authorization: Bearer {token}


---

## Common Parameters

The following parameters are *required on every request* and must be sent as query parameters or headers.

| Parameter | Type | Location | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| companyNumber | string | query / header | ✅ | Company identifier |
| salesmanCode | string | query / header | ✅ | Salesman identifier |
| Authorization | string | header | ✅ | Bearer token |

*Header format (alternative to query params)*

X-Company-Number: C001
X-Salesman-Code: S012


---

## Error Responses

All endpoints return errors in the following format:

json
{
  "status": 404,
  "code": "NOT_FOUND",
  "message": "Item 23232 not found for company C001"
}


| Status | Code | Description |
|---|---|---|
| 400 | BAD_REQUEST | Missing or invalid required parameter |
| 401 | UNAUTHORIZED | Invalid or missing token |
| 403 | FORBIDDEN | Salesman not authorized for this company |
| 404 | NOT_FOUND | Resource not found |
| 422 | VALIDATION_ERROR | Request body validation failed |
| 500 | SERVER_ERROR | Internal server error |

